Submission protocol — the plan is ONE markdown document:
1. Read the plan grammar in `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md`. The document has `type: plan` frontmatter and required `## Summary`, `## Scope`, `## Skills MCP`, `## Steps`, `## Critical Files`, `## Risks`, and `## Verification` sections. Use prose plus labeled fields; write every step as a complete `### [S-n] Title` block. `Depends on:` lists stable step IDs.
2. Author the complete document, then validate it with {{VERIFY_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`, `content` = the document). Fix every diagnostic — each names the line, section, and rule — in one repair pass.
3. Submit with {{SUBMIT_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} using the same two arguments. On success Ralph Workflow writes the canonical artifact to `.agent/artifacts/plan.md`.
4. For a targeted step change, stage the complete plan first with {{STAGE_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`, `content` = the complete document, `mode="replace_all"`). Then call {{EDIT_MD_PLAN_STEP_TOOL_REFERENCE}} against that persisted plan draft with `action` and `step_id` only. `replacement` is required for `insert` and `replace`; `index` is required for `move` and optional for a positioned `insert`; `content` is not an accepted argument. The tool saves the edited draft; inspect it with {{GET_MD_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}}, then finalize the edited draft with {{FINALIZE_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`). IDs are stable and never renumbered.
- Staged flow for long plans: build the document in chunks with {{STAGE_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`, `content` = the next chunk; `mode="replace_all"` restarts the draft), inspect with {{GET_MD_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}}, then call {{FINALIZE_MD_ARTIFACT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} (`artifact_type="plan"`) to validate and submit the assembled draft — on failure the draft is kept with the same line/section/rule diagnostics for repair. Use {{DISCARD_MD_DRAFT_TOOL_REFERENCE}} only to throw the draft away.
- Do not write `.agent/artifacts/plan.md` or any plan file directly; the submit and finalize tools are the only valid paths.
- Include `## Design` for non-trivial plans, especially when steps use `Satisfies:`, acceptance criteria are part of planning-analysis feedback, or the plan needs explicit engineering tradeoffs.

