## Plan-artifact canonical contract

Full document grammar, per-section shapes, per-list caps, and string-length tiers live in `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md`. Topics previously inlined as pointer H2 sections (Intent & intent_verb, Tightened step contract, Plan size limits, Cross-section invariants, Module family, StepType reference, Step ↔ acceptance-criteria linking, Design section) are all defined there. The closed-set reference for `step_type` is preserved inline below as `Common StepType mistakes`.

## Common StepType mistakes

- Do NOT use `Type: test`. Use `Type: verify` with `Verify: pytest tests/test_x.py -q` for test-running steps.
- Do NOT use `Type: check`, `Type: run`, or another ad-hoc label. The closed set is `file_change`, `action`, `research`, `verify`.
- If a step does not modify a file and does not run a verification command, it is `action` (a non-mutating executor action) or `research` (an exploratory step with no committed change).

Use only canonical step types: `file_change`, `action`, `research`, or `verify`. For test-running steps, write `Type: verify` and include `Verify:` or `Location:`.

