## Agent-Driven Parallel Execution

Parallel plan execution is delegated to the executing AI agent. When a plan declares parallel work, the executing agent — not Ralph Workflow — is responsible for dispatching its own sub-agents (or running the plan sequentially if it has no sub-agent capability). Ralph-managed fan-out is **dormant** in the bundled default and is retained only for future re-arming.

When you include `## Work Units` or `## Parallel Plan`, follow these rules. They describe how the agent should consume the plan, not how Ralph should run it.

**1. Declare `Directories:` for every `## Work Units` item.**
List the specific subdirectories the sub-agent may edit. The validator treats `Directories:` as optional, but a unit without it gives the executing agent no scope contract — always declare it.
```markdown
## Work Units
- [backend] Implement and test the API changes
  Directories: src/api/, tests/api/
```

**2. Keep `Directories:` values disjoint across units.**
Never declare paths where one is a prefix of the other — the validator accepts them, but overlapping units can race on the same files.
- OK: `src/api/` and `src/db/` (different trees)
- Do NOT write: `src/` and `src/api/` (one is a prefix of the other)

**3. Never declare reserved paths.**
Never list these paths under `Directories:`:
- `.agent` (reserved for Ralph Workflow internal state)
- `.git` (version control)
- `.` or empty string (entire repo — too broad)

**4. Sub-agent state is namespaced per unit.**
Each sub-agent writes its prompt documents, logs, and artifacts under `.agent/workers/<work-unit-ID>/` so results are isolated and reviewable.

**5. Phrase per-unit work so a sub-agent can execute it.**
Each `- [unit-ID] description` and its `Directories:` list must be self-contained: scope, target files, and expected outcomes. The executing agent hands each unit to a sub-agent as a complete spec.

**6. Annotate per-step evidence so the executing agent can prove completion.**
Every applicable `### [S-n]` step should include `Evidence:` bullets and, when relevant, `Verify:` so a sub-agent can run the same checks and report proof by stable step ID.

**7. Omit `## Work Units` and `## Parallel Plan` when no parallelizable work exists.**
A plan with no parallel work is valid; the executing agent runs `### [S-n]` steps in dependency order.

**8. Ralph-managed fan-out is dormant in this build.**
MUST NOT instruct the executor to route parallel plan work through Ralph-managed coordination — the bundled CLI exposes no coordination command for plan work. The executing agent's own sub-agents are the only active path for parallel plan execution in the bundled default. Re-arm by setting `[phases.<phase>.parallelization] dispatch_mode = 'ralph_fan_out'` in pipeline.toml.
